<Content>We love it! Me and my sister were there in last march for 3 days. We were a bit afraid because it was a 2 stars rated hotel and we have never been in a such low rated place, but it was the only one with vacancy room in that date and with such a short notice (we booked one day before going). We paid 鈧?5 per night with breakfast, which wasn鈥檛 bad because sleeping in Florence can be very expensive. The room is big and very nice. The bathroom was big enough and the Air-conditioned was working efficiently. We didn鈥檛 have any problems with hot water or heating, was simply perfect. It was a bit cold outside, but in our room the temperature was always something about 23 C, even when we arrived the staff had turned it on for providing that we were comfortable all the stay. The breakfast was very complete and the croissants were wonderful. The staff was very helpful and nice. The only think witch can be taken as negative point is the elevator, because only start in the first floor, and the reception is in the second one. But the staff is always trying to help to carry the bags (and ours weren鈥檛 light and short!!!). Is very close to the station of Santa Maria Novella (don鈥檛 bored to take a taxi, because is really close), in a street with lots of people and very close to the Duomo. Is a little door to a 鈥渂ig鈥?hotel. When we return to Florence we won鈥檛 look for other hotel, with more stars because we think Deco just perfect. You can go there from anywhere in Florence just walking. Florence is a city that we will never forget. Is fantastic! 
