<Author>Geneva_Diplomat
<Content>Hotel Deco - Convenient Location and Comfortable Stay Stayed 4 nights at Hotel Deco during our Italian holiday in July 2004. Very conveniently located in between the train station and the Duomo. The common areas in the hotel looked old and cramp, but we were given a rather big room (by European standards) equipped with a spacious bath room. The carpet in the room looked awful and in dire need of a good cleaning. Luckily we brought our own disposable bedroom slippers. The staff is friendly and helpful though one of them is perpetually on the phone making private calls. But on balance, a decent stay given the price we paid and since we do not have high expectations of European hotels. 
